<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>Robert La Follette's 1924 Progressive Party campaign advocated:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Business deregulation</option>
            <option letter="b">Public ownership and labor rights</option>
            <option letter="c">Conservative economic policies</option>
            <option letter="d">Immigration restrictions</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>La Follette's 1924 Progressive Party campaign advocated for public ownership of water power and railroads, stronger labor rights, farm relief, and opposition to monopolies. His platform represented a direct challenge to the conservative Republican policies of the 1920s, though his defeat highlighted the declining influence of progressivism during this period of business dominance.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
